text: Saylor is an unincorporated community in Polk County, in the U.S. state of Iowa. ==History== Saylor took its name from Saylor Township. The post office in Saylor was called Marquisville. The Marquisville post office operated from 1892 until 1907. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Polk County, Iowa Category:1892 establishments in Iowa Category:Unincorporated communities in Iowa
title: Saylor, Iowa
